HEADWORD: koppie
<hw>kop"pie</hw></mhw> <pr>(k⟦ocr⟧p"⟦icr⟧)</pr>
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[South African D., dim. of <ets>kop</ets>. See
<er>Kop</er>.]</ety> <def>A hillock; a small kop, especially a small
hill rising up from the African veld.</def> <mark>[South
Africa]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The colloqual Dutch pronunciation as here given is the
usual one in South Africa.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

